{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879422402,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa96ead001gXrlIup0JbI2jW","messageID":"msg_d7aa95d4500193Ic7jZQRVtECK","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/picod/jwt` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | S (Small) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer that provides secure token-based authentication for agentcube platform endpoints. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **Token Validation**: Support for HS256 (HMAC-SHA256) and RS256 (RSA-SHA256) JWT signature verification\n19: 2. **Claims Validation**: Verification of standard claims including expiration (`exp`), issuer (`iss`), and issued-at (`iat`) with configurable clock skew tolerance\n20: 3. **HTTP Middleware**: Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers that extracts and validates Bearer tokens from Authorization headers\n21: 4. **Configuration Management**: Environment-based configuration for JWT secrets, public keys, issuer validation, and algorithm selection\n22: 5. **Context Integration**: Propagation of parsed claims through request context for downstream handlers\n23: 6. **Standardized Error Responses**: Consistent HTTP 401/403 responses for authentication and authorization failures\n24: \n25: This middleware integrates with the PicoD command execution API (AR-015) to provide a secure authentication layer, ensuring only valid, trusted requests are processed by the agentcube platform.\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Scope\n30: \n31: ### In Scope\n32: \n33: | Item | Detail |\n34: |------|--------|\n35: | **JWTValidator Interface** | Core interface for token validation with multiple algorithms |\n36: | **HS256 Support** | HMAC-SHA256 signature verification using shared secrets |\n37: | **RS256 Support** | RSA-SHA256 signature verification using public keys |\n38: | **Token Parsing** | JWT token parsing with header and claims extraction |\n39: | **Claims Validation** | Standard claims validation (exp, iss, iat) with clock skew |\n40: | **HTTP Middleware** | Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers |\n41: | **Bearer Token Extraction** | Authorization header parsing with Bearer scheme |\n42: | **Context Propagation** | Claims injection into request context |\n43: | **Configuration Loading** | Environment variable-based configuration |\n44: | **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for validation failures |\n45: | **HTTP Responses** | Standardized JSON error responses (401/403) |\n46: \n47: ### Out of Scope\n48: \n49: - Token generation/issuance (handled by external identity provider)\n50: - Refresh token mechanism\n51: - OAuth2/OIDC integration\n52: - Session management\n53: - Rate limiting (separate middleware)\n54: - Audit logging (handled by separate layer)\n55: - JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) support (future enhancement)\n56: - Audience claim validation (future enhancement)\n57: - Multiple issuer support (future enhancement)\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Design\n62: \n63: ### File Structure\n64: \n65: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n66: |------|------|--------------|\n67: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options type definitions | ~80 |\n68: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation | ~150 |\n69: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware implementation | ~120 |\n70: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Environment-based configuration | ~80 |\n71: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error type definitions | ~60 |\n72: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests for validator | ~200 |\n73: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Unit tests for middleware | ~150 |\n74: \n75: ### Architecture\n76: \n77: ```\n78: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n79: │                    Client Application                    │\n80: │         (with JWT token from Identity Provider)          │\n81: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n82:                       │\n83:                       ▼\n84: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n85: │                    HTTP Server                           │\n86: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n87: │  │           JWTMiddleware                          │    │\n88: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────┐  │    │\n89: │  │  │   Extract   │──►│  Validate   │──►│ Verify  │  │    │\n90: │  │  │    Token    │  │   Format    │  │Signature│  │    │\n91: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └────┬────┘  │    │\n92: │  │                                         │       │    │\n93: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐      │       │    │\n94: │  │  │   Inject    │◄──│  Validate   │◄─────┘       │    │\n95: │  │  │   Claims    │  │   Claims    │              │    │\n96: │  │  │  to Context │  │ (exp, iss)  │              │    │\n97: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │    │\n98: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n99: │                          │                              │\n100: │                          ▼                              │\n101: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n102: │  │              PicoD API Handler                   │    │\n103: │  │           (AR-015 Command Execution)             │    │\n104: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n105: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### Middleware Flow\n109: \n110: ```\n111: Incoming Request\n112:        │\n113:        ▼\n114: ┌──────────────┐\n115: │ Extract      │\n116: │ Bearer Token │\n117: │ from Header  │\n118: └──────────────┘\n119:        │\n120:        ├─ Missing ──► Return 401\n121:        │\n122:        ▼\n123: ┌──────────────┐\n124: │ Validate     │\n125: │ Token Format │\n126: └──────────────┘\n127:        │\n128:        ├─ Invalid ──► Return 401\n129:        │\n130:        ▼\n131: ┌──────────────┐\n132: │ Verify       │\n133: │ Signature    │\n134: │ (HS256/RS256)│\n135: └──────────────┘\n136:        │\n137:        ├─ Invalid ──► Return 401\n138:        │\n139:        ▼\n140: ┌──────────────┐\n141: │ Validate     │\n142: │ Claims       │\n143: │ (exp, iss)   │\n144: └──────────────┘\n145:        │\n146:        ├─ Expired ──► Return 401\n147:        ├─ Bad Issuer ► Return 403\n148:        │\n149:        ▼\n150: ┌──────────────┐\n151: │ Call Handler │\n152: │ with Claims  │\n153: │ in Context   │\n154: └──────────────┘\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### Core Types\n158: \n159: #### JWTValidator Interface\n160: \n161: ```go\n162: type JWTValidator interface {\n163:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n164:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: #### Claims Structure\n169: \n170: ```go\n171: type Claims struct {\n172:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`  // User/subject identifier\n173:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`  // Token issuer\n174:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`  // Expiration timestamp\n175:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`  // Issued-at timestamp\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: #### ValidationOptions\n180: \n181: ```go\n182: type ValidationOptions struct {\n183:     Algorithm      string           // \"HS256\" or \"RS256\"\n184:     Secret         []byte           // HMAC secret for HS256\n185:     PublicKey      *rsa.PublicKey   // RSA public key for RS256\n186:     ExpectedIssuer string           // Expected issuer claim\n187:     ClockSkew      time.Duration    // Allowed clock skew (default 1m)\n188:     AllowedAlgs    []string         // Allowed algorithms whitelist\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: #### MiddlewareOptions\n193: \n194: ```go\n195: type MiddlewareOptions struct {\n196:     Validator    JWTValidator\n197:     ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: #### NewValidator Constructor\n202: \n203: ```go\n204: // NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with the specified options\n205: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n206: ```\n207: \n208: #### Middleware Function\n209: \n210: ```go\n211: // JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation\n212: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n213: \n214: // GetClaims retrieves validated claims from request context\n215: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## Execution Flows\n221: \n222: ### Token Validation (HS256)\n223: \n224: ```\n225: ValidateToken(token)\n226:     │\n227:     ▼\n228: Parse JWT header to extract algorithm\n229:     │\n230:     ▼\n231: Verify algorithm is in AllowedAlgs\n232:     │\n233:     ├─ Unsupported ──► Return ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n234:     │\n235:     ▼\n236: Verify algorithm matches configured Algorithm\n237:     │\n238:     ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n239:     │\n240:     ▼\n241: Parse JWT claims\n242:     │\n243:     ├─ Malformed ──► Return ErrInvalidTokenFormat\n244:     │\n245:     ▼\n246: Verify HMAC signature using configured Secret\n247:     │\n248:     ├─ Invalid ──► Return ErrInvalidSignature\n249:     │\n250:     ▼\n251: Validate exp claim (with ClockSkew tolerance)\n252:     │\n253:     ├─ Expired ──► Return ErrTokenExpired\n254:     │\n255:     ▼\n256: Validate iss claim against ExpectedIssuer\n257:     │\n258:     ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrInvalidIssuer\n259:     │\n260:     ▼\n261: Return parsed Claims\n262: ```\n263: \n264: ### Token Validation (RS256)\n265: \n266: ```\n267: ValidateToken(token)\n268:     │\n269:     ▼\n270: Parse JWT header to extract algorithm\n271:     │\n272:     ▼\n273: Verify algorithm is RSA-based and allowed\n274:     │\n275:     ▼\n276: Parse JWT claims\n277:     │\n278:     ▼\n279: Verify RSA signature using configured PublicKey\n280:     │\n281:     ├─ Invalid ──► Return ErrInvalidSignature\n282:     │\n283:     ▼\n284: Validate exp claim (with ClockSkew tolerance)\n285:     │\n286:     ├─ Expired ──► Return ErrTokenExpired\n287:     │\n288:     ▼\n289: Validate iss claim against ExpectedIssuer\n290:     │\n291:     ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrInvalidIssuer\n292:     │\n293:     ▼\n294: Return parsed Claims\n295: ```\n296: \n297: ### HTTP Middleware Processing\n298: \n299: ```\n300: JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n301:     │\n302:     ▼\n303: Incoming HTTP request\n304:     │\n305:     ▼\n306: Extract Authorization header\n307:     │\n308:     ├─ Missing ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n309:     │\n310:     ▼\n311: Check Bearer prefix\n312:     │\n313:     ├─ Missing/Invalid ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n314:     │\n315:     ▼\n316: Extract token string\n317:     │\n318:     ▼\n319: Call validator.ValidateToken(token)\n320:     │\n321:     ├─ ErrInvalidSignature ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n322:     ├─ ErrTokenExpired ──────► Return 401 + JSON error\n323:     ├─ ErrInvalidIssuer ─────► Return 403 + JSON error\n324:     ├─ Other errors ─────────► Return 401 + JSON error\n325:     │\n326:     ▼\n327: Add claims to request context\n328:     │\n329:     ▼\n330: Call wrapped handler with enhanced context\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ## Error Handling\n336: \n337: ### Error Types\n338: \n339: | Error | Code | Description |\n340: |-------|------|-------------|\n341: | `ErrMissingToken` | `MISSING_TOKEN` | No Authorization header present |\n342: | `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | `INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT` | Malformed Authorization header or JWT |\n343: | `ErrInvalidSignature` | `INVALID_SIGNATURE` | Signature verification failed |\n344: | `ErrTokenExpired` | `TOKEN_EXPIRED` | Token has expired |\n345: | `ErrInvalidIssuer` | `INVALID_ISSUER` | Issuer claim mismatch |\n346: | `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | `UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM` | Algorithm not in allowed list |\n347: \n348: ### HTTP Responses\n349: \n350: | Scenario | Status | Body |\n351: |----------|--------|------|\n352: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n353: | Invalid format | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token format\"}` |\n354: | Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n355: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n356: | Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n357: | Unsupported algorithm | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"unsupported algorithm\"}` |\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ## Security Considerations\n362: \n363: ### Token Transmission\n364: - Tokens MUST be transmitted via HTTPS in production\n365: - HTTP in development only with appropriate warnings\n366: \n367: ### Key Management\n368: - HMAC secrets MUST be securely stored (e.g., Kubernetes secrets)\n369: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n370: - Private keys for token signing are NOT handled by this middleware\n371: \n372: ### Validation Security\n373: - Short token expiration recommended (minutes to hours)\n374: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal (default 1 minute)\n375: - Algorithm explicitly specified to prevent \"none\" algorithm attacks\n376: - Allowed algorithms whitelist prevents unexpected algorithm usage\n377: \n378: ### Path Security\n379: - Workspace isolation ensures tokens are scoped appropriately\n380: - Claims context propagation follows request lifecycle\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## Impact Analysis\n385: \n386: ### Files Created\n387: \n388: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n389: |------|--------------|-------------|\n390: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | ~80 | Claims and options type definitions |\n391: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | ~150 | JWTValidator implementation |\n392: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | ~120 | HTTP middleware implementation |\n393: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | ~80 | Environment-based configuration |\n394: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | ~60 | Error type definitions |\n395: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | ~200 | Unit tests for validator |\n396: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | ~150 | Unit tests for middleware |\n397: \n398: ### Dependencies\n399: \n400: ```go\n401: import (\n402:     \"context\"\n403:     \"crypto/rsa\"\n404:     \"errors\"\n405:     \"fmt\"\n406:     \"net/http\"\n407:     \"strings\"\n408:     \"time\"\n409:     \n410:     \"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n411: )\n412: ```\n413: \n414: | Package | Purpose |\n415: |---------|---------|\n416: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation library |\n417: \n418: ### Downstream Consumers\n419: \n420: | Consumer | Usage |\n421: |----------|-------|\n422: | PicoD API Server | Protects command execution endpoints (AR-015) |\n423: | Session Manager | Validates tokens for session operations |\n424: | CLI Tooling | Token-aware request handling |\n425: \n426: ### Performance Characteristics\n427: \n428: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n429: |-----------|------------|-------|\n430: | Token parsing | O(1) | Fixed JWT structure parsing |\n431: | HS256 validation | O(1) | Fast HMAC computation |\n432: | RS256 validation | O(1) | Slower RSA signature verification |\n433: | Context propagation | O(1) | Simple pointer passing |\n434: \n435: ### Algorithm Performance Comparison\n436: \n437: | Algorithm | Relative Speed | Use Case |\n438: |-----------|----------------|----------|\n439: | HS256 | Fast (1x) | Internal services, symmetric trust |\n440: | RS256 | Slower (~10x) | External clients, asymmetric trust |\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## Alternatives Considered\n445: \n446: ### Alternative 1: Use Standard OAuth2/OIDC Middleware\n447: \n448: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n449: |--------|------------|\n450: | **Pros** | Full standard compliance; broader ecosystem support; automatic token refresh handling |\n451: | **Cons** | Heavy dependency footprint; more complex configuration; unnecessary features for our use case |\n452: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Custom JWT middleware provides sufficient functionality with minimal dependencies |\n453: \n454: ### Alternative 2: Implement Custom JWT Parsing (No Library)\n455: \n456: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n457: |--------|------------|\n458: | **Pros** | Zero external dependencies; full control over implementation; minimal binary size |\n459: | **Cons** | Security risk if implementation flawed; maintenance burden; lacks battle-tested validation |\n460: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Using established `golang-jwt/jwt` library provides security and reliability |\n461: \n462: ### Alternative 3: API Gateway-Level Authentication\n463: \n464: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n465: |--------|------------|\n466: | **Pros** | Centralized authentication; service doesn't handle auth logic; works with existing gateways |\n467: | **Cons** | Requires gateway deployment; less flexible per-endpoint configuration; claims not available to service |\n468: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — In-middleware approach provides better integration with PicoD context and per-handler flexibility |\n469: \n470: ### Alternative 4: Session-Based Authentication (Cookies)\n471: \n472: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n473: |--------|------------|\n474: | **Pros** | Stateless clients; simpler for browser-based clients; built-in session management |\n475: | **Cons** | Requires session storage; CSRF concerns; less suitable for API-only clients |\n476: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — JWT tokens better fit the stateless API architecture and cross-service authentication needs |\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## Risks and Mitigations\n481: \n482: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n483: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n484: | Weak HMAC secrets | Low | Critical | Configuration validation; minimum secret length enforcement; secure secret generation guidance |\n485: | RSA key confusion attacks | Low | High | Explicit algorithm configuration; algorithm whitelist; reject \"none\" algorithm |\n486: | Clock skew causing token rejection | Medium | Medium | Configurable clock skew tolerance; clear documentation on time synchronization |\n487: | Token replay attacks | Low | Medium | Short token expiration; consider token binding in future |\n488: | Algorithm confusion attacks | Low | Critical | Strict algorithm validation; separate code paths for HS256/RS256 |\n489: | Key extraction from memory | Low | High | Use secure string handling; minimize key exposure time |\n490: | JWT library vulnerabilities | Low | Critical | Use well-maintained library; regular dependency updates; CVE monitoring |\n491: | Configuration errors on startup | Medium | High | Fail-fast validation; clear error messages; configuration documentation |\n492: \n493: ---\n494: \n495: ## Verification\n496: \n497: ### Unit Tests\n498: \n499: ```bash\n500: # Run all JWT middleware tests\n501: make test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n502: \n503: # Run with race detector\n504: go test -race ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n505: \n506: # Run specific test categories\n507: go test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestValidateToken\"\n508: go test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestMiddleware\"\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### Integration Tests\n512: \n513: ```bash\n514: # Run integration tests\n515: make integration-test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n516: \n517: # With coverage\n518: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n519: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n520: ```\n521: \n522: ### Manual Verification\n523: \n524: ```bash\n525: # Build verification\n526: go build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n527: \n528: # Interface compliance check\n529: go build ./...\n530: \n531: # Lint check\n532: make lint PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Test Scenarios\n536: \n537: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n538: |----------|-----------------|\n539: | Valid HS256 token | Returns parsed Claims with no error |\n540: | Valid RS256 token | Returns parsed Claims with no error |\n541: | Invalid HS256 signature | Returns ErrInvalidSignature |\n542: | Invalid RS256 signature | Returns ErrInvalidSignature |\n543: | Expired token | Returns ErrTokenExpired |\n544: | Token with clock skew within tolerance | Returns parsed Claims |\n545: | Wrong issuer | Returns ErrInvalidIssuer |\n546: | Unsupported algorithm | Returns ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm |\n547: | Request with valid token (middleware) | Proceeds to handler with claims in context |\n548: | Request without token (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n549: | Request with invalid format (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n550: | Request with expired token (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n551: | Request with wrong issuer (middleware) | Returns 403 with JSON error |\n552: | Configuration loading from environment | Correctly parses all settings |\n553: | Missing required configuration | Returns error on startup |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## References\n558: \n559: - [PicoD JWT Design](changes/AR-017/design.md) — Detailed design document\n560: - [PicoD JWT Delta Spec](changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n561: - [PicoD JWT Tests](changes/AR-017/tests.md) — Test specifications\n562: - [PicoD JWT Plan](changes/AR-017/plan.md) — Implementation plan\n563: - [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Base API that this middleware protects\n564: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns for agentcube\n565: \n566: ---\n567: \n568: ## Success Criteria\n569: \n570: 1. ✅ JWTValidator interface fully implemented with HS256 and RS256 support\n571: 2. ✅ Token validation correctly verifies signatures for both algorithms\n572: 3. ✅ Claims validation (exp, iss, iat) with configurable clock skew\n573: 4. ✅ HTTP middleware extracts and validates Bearer tokens\n574: 5. ✅ Context propagation allows handlers to access parsed claims\n575: 6. ✅ Environment-based configuration with validation\n576: 7. ✅ Standardized HTTP 401/403 error responses\n577: 8. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n578: 9. ✅ Integration tests passing\n579: 10. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n580: 11. ✅ Documentation complete with usage examples\n581: \n582: ---\n583: \n584: *AR-017 — Module: pkg/picod/jwt — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 584 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod/jwt` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer that provides secure token-based authentication for agentcube platform endpoints. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Token Validation**: Support for HS256 (HMAC-SHA256) and RS256 (RSA-SHA256) JWT signature verification\n2. **Claims Validation**: Verification of standard claims including expiration (`exp`), issuer (`iss`), and issued-at (`iat`) with configurable clock skew tolerance\n3. **HTTP Middleware**: Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers that extracts and validates Bearer tokens from Authorization headers","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775879422354,"end":1775879422400}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879422406,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa9724a001h6spLnPhOc3uiz","messageID":"msg_d7aa95d4500193Ic7jZQRVtECK","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775879422357,"end":1775879422404}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879422409,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa9764c001ZzXSiLsVMfJYxl","messageID":"msg_d7aa95d4500193Ic7jZQRVtECK","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: Run a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n5: \n6: ## Requirements\n7: \n8: ### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\n9: The system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n10: \n11: #### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n12: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n13: - **WHEN** the manager is running\n14: - **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n15: \n16: ### Requirement: Idle detection input\n17: The system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n20: - **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`\n21: - **WHEN** reconciliation completes\n22: - **THEN** the sandbox is not deleted and result has zero `RequeueAfter`\n23: \n24: ### Requirement: Idle detection parsing\n25: When the annotation is non-empty, the system SHALL parse it with `time.RFC3339`. On parse error, the system SHALL return `RequeueAfter: 30 seconds` and the parse error.\n26: \n27: #### Scenario: Invalid timestamp requeues\n28: - **GIVEN** annotation value is not RFC3339\n29: - **WHEN** `time.Parse` fails\n30: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(Result{RequeueAfter: 30s}, err)`\n31: \n32: ### Requirement: Expiration threshold\n33: The system SHALL define `SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`. The system SHALL compute `expirationTime = lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`. When `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`, the system SHALL delete the `Sandbox` resource.\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Idle beyond 15 minutes triggers delete\n36: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` parses to a time more than 15 minutes in the past\n37: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n38: - **THEN** the controller calls delete on the `Sandbox` client object\n39: \n40: #### Scenario: Not yet expired requeues until expiration\n41: - **GIVEN** `last-activity-time` is recent enough that expiration is in the future\n42: - **WHEN** reconciliation runs\n43: - **THEN** the result is `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)` and no delete occurs\n44: \n45: ### Requirement: Delete idempotency\n46: When delete returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL treat it as success and SHALL return empty result with nil error. Other delete errors SHALL be returned to trigger retry.\n47: \n48: #### Scenario: Already deleted sandbox\n49: - **GIVEN** the API server returns not found on delete\n50: - **WHEN** the reconciler handles the error\n51: - **THEN** reconcile returns `(ctrl.Result{}, nil)`\n52: \n53: ### Requirement: Get not found\n54: When get returns `NotFound`, the system SHALL return empty result and nil error.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: Sandbox removed before reconcile\n57: - **GIVEN** the sandbox no longer exists\n58: - **WHEN** `Get` fails with not found\n59: - **THEN** reconcile returns without error\n60: \n61: ## Requirements (binary / operator)\n62: \n63: ### Requirement: Manager options\n64: The `agentd` binary SHALL construct controller-runtime `Manager` with scheme containing core Kubernetes types and `sandboxv1alpha1` from `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`, SHALL disable metrics server (`BindAddress: \"0\"`), and SHALL disable health probe server (`HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\"`).\n65: \n66: #### Scenario: Signal-driven shutdown\n67: - **GIVEN** the process runs `mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())`\n68: - **WHEN** SIGTERM/SIGINT is received\n69: - **THEN** the manager stops gracefully per controller-runtime defaults\n\n(End of file - total 69 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup Specification\n\n## Purpose\nRun a controller that deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when an idle-timeout annotation indicates the sandbox has been inactive beyond a fixed grace period.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Reconciliation trigger\nThe system SHALL register a controller-runtime reconciler for resource kind `Sandbox` API version `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, using the manager’s API reader/writer client for get/delete operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox watch drives reconcile\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` object is created or updated in the cluster\n- **WHEN** the manager is running\n- **THEN** the reconciler `Reconcile` function is invoked with the object’s namespace and name\n\n### Requirement: Idle detection input\nThe system SHALL read annotation key `last-activity-time` (constant `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey`) from the `Sandbox` metadata. When the annotation is missing or empty, the system SHALL take no delete action and SHALL return without requeue (unless other logic applies—none in this controller).\n\n#### Scenario: No annotation means no deletion\n- **GIVEN** a `Sandbox` without `last-activity-time`","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/spec.md","time":{"start":1775879422371,"end":1775879422406}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775879422439,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa981c8001RUoZF9Ai276q0O","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7aa95d4500193Ic7jZQRVtECK","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":22213,"input":4,"output":229,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":4627,"read":17353}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775879425843,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa98f30001zwfOo5LVk68qnA","messageID":"msg_d7aa981ff001HlV7QDtHPom2C2","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879432279,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa99fb8001ynKt2OPjvxJUSr","messageID":"msg_d7aa981ff001HlV7QDtHPom2C2","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n2: \n3: > Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n4: > Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n5: \n6: ## Purpose\n7: \n8: AgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\n9: It provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\n10: session-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n11: \n12: ## Tech Stack\n13: \n14: | Layer | Technology |\n15: |-------|-----------|\n16: | Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n17: | Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n18: | HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n19: | Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n20: | Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |\n21: | Auth | JWT RS256 (golang-jwt/v5), K8s TokenReview |\n22: | Packaging | Helm 3, multi-stage Docker, GitHub Actions CI/CD |\n23: | Docs | Docusaurus 3.x |\n24: \n25: ## Architecture\n26: \n27: ```\n28: Client / SDK / CLI\n29:   → Router (Deployment :8080)\n30:      ↔ Redis/Valkey (session store)\n31:      → WorkloadManager (Service :8080)\n32:         ↔ Redis/Valkey\n33:         → K8s API: CRDs, Sandbox, Pod, Secret, TokenReview\n34:   Sandbox Pods (with optional PicoD daemon)\n35:   Agentd (idle cleanup controller)\n36:   Optional: Volcano vc-agent-scheduler\n37: ```\n38: \n39: ## Conventions\n40: \n41: - Go packages under `pkg/`, binaries under `cmd/`\n42: - Python CLI at `cmd/cli/`, SDK at `sdk-python/`\n43: - JSON tags use camelCase; Go structs use PascalCase\n44: - K8s resources use `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` API group\n45: - Normative language: SHALL = mandatory, SHOULD = recommended, MAY = optional\n\n(End of file - total 45 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube — OpenSpec Project Context\n\n> Source: [github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube)\n> Generated: 2026-03-21 (from source tree reverse-engineering)\n\n## Purpose\n\nAgentCube is a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform for AI agents.\nIt provisions isolated sandbox pods on demand, routes HTTP traffic to them through\nsession-aware proxies, and manages their lifecycle (creation, expiry, idle cleanup).\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Language (server) | Go 1.24, module `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` |\n| Language (CLI/SDK) | Python ≥3.10 |\n| HTTP framework | Gin (Go), Typer (Python CLI), FastAPI (example) |\n| Kubernetes | CRDs (`runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`), controller-runtime, `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox` |\n| Storage | Redis (go-redis/v9), Valkey (valkey-go) |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/project.md","time":{"start":1775879432266,"end":1775879432277}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879432291,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa9a3c6001s0QZJjeUgEo2yl","messageID":"msg_d7aa981ff001HlV7QDtHPom2C2","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n16: │                           │                              │\n17: │                           ▼                              │\n18: │                   Token Validation                       │\n19: │                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Middleware Flow\n24: \n25: ```\n26: Incoming Request\n27:        │\n28:        ▼\n29: ┌──────────────┐\n30: │ Extract      │\n31: │ Bearer Token │\n32: └──────────────┘\n33:        │\n34:        ▼\n35: ┌──────────────┐\n36: │ Validate     │\n37: │ Token Format │\n38: └──────────────┘\n39:        │\n40:        ▼\n41: ┌──────────────┐\n42: │ Verify       │\n43: │ Signature    │\n44: └──────────────┘\n45:        │\n46:        ▼\n47: ┌──────────────┐\n48: │ Validate     │\n49: │ Claims       │\n50: │ (exp, iss)   │\n51: └──────────────┘\n52:        │\n53:        ▼\n54:    [Valid] ────► Call Handler\n55:        │\n56:    [Invalid] ──► Return 401/403\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ## Key Interfaces\n60: \n61: ### JWTValidator\n62: \n63: Core interface for token validation.\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type JWTValidator interface {\n67:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n68:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Middleware Function\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: // Middleware wraps an HTTP handler with JWT validation\n76: func JWTMiddleware(validator JWTValidator, opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Claims Structure\n80: \n81: ```go\n82: type Claims struct {\n83:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n84:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n85:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n86:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Validation Options\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type ValidationOptions struct {\n94:     Issuer        string        // Expected issuer claim\n95:     ClockSkew     time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for exp validation\n96:     AllowedAlgs   []string      // Allowed signing algorithms\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ## Supported Algorithms\n101: \n102: | Algorithm | Type | Key Format |\n103: |-----------|------|------------|\n104: | HS256 | HMAC-SHA256 | []byte (symmetric) |\n105: | RS256 | RSA-SHA256 | *rsa.PublicKey |\n106: \n107: ## Configuration\n108: \n109: ### Environment Variables\n110: \n111: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n112: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n113: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 only | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n114: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 only | - | Path to RSA public key file |\n115: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n116: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | 1m | Clock skew tolerance |\n117: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | RS256 | Signing algorithm |\n118: \n119: ## Error Handling\n120: \n121: ### Error Types\n122: \n123: - `ErrMissingToken`: No Authorization header present\n124: - `ErrInvalidTokenFormat`: Malformed Authorization header\n125: - `ErrInvalidSignature`: Signature verification failed\n126: - `ErrTokenExpired`: Token has expired\n127: - `ErrInvalidIssuer`: Issuer claim mismatch\n128: - `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`: Algorithm not in allowed list\n129: \n130: ### HTTP Responses\n131: \n132: | Scenario | Status | Body |\n133: |----------|--------|------|\n134: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n135: | Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n136: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n137: | Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n138: \n139: ## Security Considerations\n140: \n141: - Tokens must be transmitted via HTTPS\n142: - HMAC secrets must be securely stored\n143: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n144: - Short token expiration recommended\n145: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal\n146: \n147: ## Performance Considerations\n148: \n149: - RSA signature verification is slower than HMAC\n150: - Consider caching parsed keys\n151: - Minimize allocations in hot path\n152: - Early rejection for missing headers\n153: \n154: ## Open Questions\n155: \n156: 1. Should we support JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) for key rotation?\n157: 2. Do we need audience claim validation?\n158: 3. Should we support multiple issuers?\n159: 4. Is token binding to specific endpoints required?\n\n(End of file - total 159 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n│                           │                              │\n│                           ▼                              │\n│                   Token Validation                       │\n│                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775879432269,"end":1775879432289}}}}
