{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879444506,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa9d572001j6ShhBVzarWGD4","messageID":"msg_d7aa9c326001dsWckGP975og4R","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed. Let me write the proposal.md for AR-018 following the format of AR-017.","time":{"start":1775879444504,"end":1775879444504}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879554502,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaaaf34001uEYsIqzcObHc0k","messageID":"msg_d7aa9c326001dsWckGP975og4R","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"text","text":" Startup","time":{"start":1775879554497,"end":1775879554497}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879554603,"sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","part":{"id":"prt_d7aa9d81b001lNW7rvLJbhOPLs","messageID":"msg_d7aa9c326001dsWckGP975og4R","sessionID":"ses_28556d22bffevyS1U2GDohG19W","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","content":"# Proposal: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## AR-018 — Agentd 空闲清理控制器\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/agentd` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Agentd idle cleanup controller that automatically deletes `Sandbox` custom resources when they have been inactive beyond a configured timeout. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Reconciler Controller**: A controller-runtime reconciler that watches `Sandbox` resources and manages their lifecycle based on activity timestamps\n2. **Idle Detection**: Reading and parsing the `last-activity-time` annotation to determine when a sandbox was last active\n3. **Automatic Cleanup**: Deleting sandboxes that have exceeded the `SessionExpirationTimeout` (15 minutes)\n4. **Efficient Requeueing**: Scheduling reconciliation at the exact expiration time to minimize unnecessary API calls\n5. **Error Handling**: Graceful handling of parse errors, not-found errors, and deletion failures\n6. **Binary Integration**: A standalone `agentd` binary that runs the controller using controller-runtime manager\n\nThis controller integrates with the agentcube platform to ensure sandboxes don't consume resources indefinitely when idle, complementing the workload manager's sandbox creation and session management capabilities.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In Scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Reconciler** | controller-runtime `Reconciler` implementation for Sandbox resources |\n| **Idle Detection** | Reading `last-activity-time` annotation from Sandbox metadata |\n| **Time Parsing** | RFC3339 timestamp parsing with error handling |\n| **Expiration Logic** | Computing expiration time based on `SessionExpirationTimeout` |\n| **Resource Deletion** | Deleting Sandbox resources via Kubernetes client |\n| **Requeue Scheduling** | Smart requeue at expiration time for pending cleanups |\n| **Error Handling** | Proper handling of NotFound, parse errors, and delete errors |\n| **Manager Setup** | Controller-runtime manager configuration and startup |\n| **Scheme Registration** | Registration of Sandbox CRD types |\n| **Binary Entrypoint** | `cmd/agentd/main.go` with signal-driven shutdown |\n\n### Out of Scope\n\n- Activity tracking/timestamp updates (handled by workload manager)\n- Custom idle timeout per sandbox (uses fixed 15-minute threshold)\n- Graceful shutdown of sandbox workloads before deletion\n- Cleanup of related Kubernetes resources (pods, secrets) - handled by ownerReferences\n- Metrics and monitoring endpoints\n- Leader election for multi-replica deployments\n- Webhook validation for Sandbox resources\n- Horizontal scaling considerations\n\n---\n\n## Design\n\n### File Structure\n\n| File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n|------|------|--------------|\n| `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | Reconciler implementation | ~100 |\n| `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | Unit tests for reconciler | ~150 |\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | Binary entrypoint | ~60 |\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Kubernetes Cluster                    │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │              Agentd Controller                   │    │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────┐  │    │\n│  │  │         Controller-Runtime Manager         │  │    │\n│  │  │  ┌─────────┐  ┌─────────┐  ┌───────────┐  │  │    │\n│  │  │  │  Watch  │──►│Reconcile│──►│  Delete   │  │  │    │\n│  │  │  │ Sandbox │  │         │  │  Sandbox  │  │  │    │\n│  │  │  └─────────┘  └────┬────┘  └───────────┘  │  │    │\n│  │  │                    │                      │  │    │\n│  │  │              ┌─────┴─────┐                │  │    │\n│  │  │              ▼           ▼                │  │    │\n│  │  │        ┌──────────┐  ┌──────────┐         │  │    │\n│  │  │        │Parse Time│  │Schedule  │         │  │    │\n│  │  │        │RFC3339   │  │Requeue   │         │  │    │\n│  │  │        └──────────┘  └──────────┘         │  │    │\n│  │  └───────────────────────────────────────────┘  │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n│                           │                              │\n│                           ▼                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n│  │            Sandbox CRD (agents.x-k8s.io)         │    │\n│  │  metadata:                                       │    │\n│  │    annotations:                                  │    │\n│  │      last-activity-time: \"2026-03-21T10:00:00Z\" │    │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Reconciliation Flow\n\n```\nReconcile(request)\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Get Sandbox  │\n└──────────────┘\n        │\n        ├─ NotFound ──► Return (empty, nil)\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────┐\n│ Read last-activity-time  │\n│ annotation               │\n└──────────────────────────┘\n        │\n        ├─ Missing/Empty ──► Return (empty, nil)\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────┐\n│ Parse Time   │\n│ (RFC3339)    │\n└──────────────┘\n        │\n        ├─ Parse Error ──► Return (RequeueAfter: 30s, err)\n        │\n        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────┐\n│ Compute Expiration:     │\n│ lastActivity + 15min    │\n└─────────────────────────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n   Expired?\n        │\n   ┌────┴────┐\n   ▼         ▼\n  Yes       No\n   │         │\n   ▼         ▼\n┌──────┐  ┌──────────────────┐\n│Delete│  │Return RequeueAfter│\n│      │  │time.Until(expire) │\n└──┬───┘  └──────────────────┘\n   │\n   ▼\n┌─────────────┐\n│ NotFound?   │\n└──────┬──────┘\n       │\n  ┌────┴────┐\n  ▼         ▼\n Yes        No\n  │          │\n  ▼          ▼\n┌──────┐  ┌─────────┐\n│Return│  │Return   │\n│ok    │  │error    │\n└──────┘  └─────────┘\n```\n\n### Core Types\n\n#### Reconciler Struct\n\n```go\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    client.Client\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n}\n```\n\n#### Key Constants\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\n#### Reconcile Method Signature\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n```\n\n#### SetupWithManager\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n    return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n        For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n        Complete(r)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Execution Flows\n\n### Successful Idle Cleanup\n\n```\nReconcile(ctx, req)\n    │\n    ▼\nsandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}\nGet(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nlastActivityStr := sandbox.Annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n    │\n    ▼\nlastActivity, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n    │\n    ▼\nexpirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)\n    │\n    ▼\ntime.Now().After(expirationTime) == true\n    │\n    ▼\nr.Delete(ctx, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn ctrl.Result{}, nil\n```\n\n### Future Expiration (Requeue)\n\n```\nReconcile(ctx, req)\n    │\n    ▼\nsandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}\nGet(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)\n    │\n    ▼\nlastActivityStr := sandbox.Annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n    │\n    ▼\nlastActivity, _ := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n    │\n    ▼\nexpirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)\n    │\n    ▼\ntime.Now().After(expirationTime) == false\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn ctrl.Result{\n    RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime),\n}, nil\n```\n\n### Parse Error Recovery\n\n```\nReconcile(ctx, req)\n    │\n    ▼\nlastActivityStr := sandbox.Annotations[\"last-activity-time\"]\n    │\n    ▼\nlastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)\n    │\n    ▼\nerr != nil (malformed timestamp)\n    │\n    ▼\nReturn ctrl.Result{\n    RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second,\n}, err\n```\n\n### Binary Startup Flow\n\n```\nmain()\n    │\n    ▼\nschemeBuilder := runtime.NewScheme()\n    │\n    ▼\nscheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder)\nsandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder)\n    │\n    ▼\nmgr, _ := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n    Scheme: schemeBuilder,\n    Metrics: metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n    HealthProbeBindAddress: \"0\",\n})\n    │\n    ▼\nctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n    For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n    Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n        Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n        Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n    })\n    │\n    ▼\nmgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Types\n\n| Error | Description |\n|-------|-------------|\n| `NotFound` | Sandbox already deleted or never existed |\n| `ParseError` | Invalid RFC3339 timestamp in annotation |\n| `DeleteError` | Kubernetes API delete operation failed |\n\n### HTTP Responses\n\n| Scenario | Result | Error |\n|----------|--------|-------|\n| Sandbox not found | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n| No activity annotation | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n| Invalid timestamp | `RequeueAfter: 30s` | parse error |\n| Not yet expired | `RequeueAfter: time.Until(expiration)` | `nil` |\n| Delete succeeded | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n| Delete NotFound | `ctrl.Result{}` | `nil` |\n| Delete other error | `ctrl.Result{}` | delete error |\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\nThe `agentd` controller requires the following RBAC permissions:\n\n| Resource | Verbs | Reason |\n|----------|-------|--------|\n| `sandboxes` | `get`, `list`, `watch`, `delete` | Core reconciler operations |\n| `sandboxes/status` | `get`, `update` | Future status updates |\n\n### Annotation Trust\n\n- The `last-activity-time` annotation is set by the workload manager, which is trusted\n- The reconciler only reads this annotation; it does not modify it\n- No validation of annotation origin is performed (relies on Kubernetes RBAC)\n\n### Resource Cleanup\n\n- Deletion of Sandbox triggers cascade deletion of owned resources via ownerReferences\n- No direct deletion of Pods, Secrets, or other child resources\n- Follows standard Kubernetes garbage collection patterns\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Files Created\n\n| File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n|------|--------------|-------------|\n| `pkg/agentd/reconciler.go` | ~100 | Reconciler implementation |\n| `pkg/agentd/reconciler_test.go` | ~150 | Unit tests for reconciler |\n| `cmd/agentd/main.go` | ~60 | Binary entrypoint |\n\n### Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/metrics/server\"\n    \n    \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Kubernetes controller framework |\n| `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1` | Sandbox CRD types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes API machinery |\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Usage |\n|----------|-------|\n| Workload Manager | Sets `last-activity-time` annotation on sandboxes |\n| Sandbox CRD | Resource being reconciled and deleted |\n| Kubernetes GC | Cleans up owned resources after Sandbox deletion |\n\n### Performance Characteristics\n\n| Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n|-----------|------------|-------|\n| Get Sandbox | O(1) | Single API call by name |\n| Delete Sandbox | O(1) | Single API call |\n| Requeue scheduling | O(1) | Computed from timestamp |\n| Memory usage | O(1) | Per-reconciler constant |\n\n### Watched Resources\n\n| API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n|-----------|---------|------|---------|\n| `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Creates, updates, deletes |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Alternative 1: CronJob-based Cleanup\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Simpler implementation; no long-running process; uses existing Kubernetes primitives |\n| **Cons** | Polling overhead (fixed intervals); delayed cleanup (worst-case interval delay); requires cluster-wide list permissions |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Event-driven reconciler provides immediate response to sandbox changes and precise expiration scheduling |\n\n### Alternative 2: OwnerReference with TTL\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Native Kubernetes feature; no custom controller needed; automatic garbage collection |\n| **Cons** | TTL is from creation time, not last activity; doesn't support idle-based cleanup; requires newer Kubernetes versions |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — TTL doesn't match idle-cleanup semantics; we need activity-based, not creation-based expiration |\n\n### Alternative 3: Webhook-based Pre-Delete Validation\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Can block deletion if activity recent; validates before allowing delete |\n| **Cons** | More complex; requires webhook server; doesn't handle automatic cleanup |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Adds unnecessary complexity; reconciler pattern is standard for this use case |\n\n### Alternative 4: Workload Manager Handles Cleanup\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| **Pros** | Single component manages full lifecycle; no separate binary |\n| **Cons** | Violates separation of concerns; workload manager focuses on creation, not long-term maintenance; harder to scale independently |\n| **Decision** | **Rejected** — Dedicated controller follows Kubernetes best practices for resource lifecycle management |\n\n---\n\n## Risks and Mitigations\n\n| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|--------|------------|\n| Clock skew between controller and workload manager | Low | Medium | Both use Kubernetes API server time; RFC3339 includes timezone |\n| Requeue storm on many expiring sandboxes | Low | Medium | Natural spread from different creation times; controller-runtime rate limiting |\n| Sandbox deleted while active | Low | High | 15-minute grace period provides buffer; activity updates are frequent |\n| Parse errors from malformed timestamps | Low | Low | Requeue with 30s delay; eventually consistent |\n| API server unavailable | Low | High | Controller-runtime exponential backoff; eventual reconciliation |\n| Race condition between activity update and cleanup | Low | Medium | Requeue if not yet expired; next activity update will be seen |\n| Missing RBAC permissions | Medium | High | Clear error on startup; fail-fast in main.go |\n\n---\n\n## Verification\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run all agentd tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/agentd/...\n\n# Run specific test categories\ngo test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestReconcile\"\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```bash\n# Run integration tests\nmake integration-test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/agentd/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n```\n\n### Manual Verification\n\n```bash\n# Build verification\ngo build ./cmd/agentd/...\n\n# Run locally (requires kubeconfig)\n./agentd\n\n# Lint check\nmake lint PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n```\n\n### Test Scenarios\n\n| Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----------|-----------------|\n| Sandbox without annotation | No deletion, empty result |\n| Sandbox with valid recent timestamp | Requeue after time.Until(expiration) |\n| Sandbox expired (15+ min idle) | Delete called, success |\n| Sandbox already deleted | No error, empty result |\n| Invalid timestamp format | Requeue after 30s, error returned |\n| Delete returns NotFound | No error, empty result |\n| Delete returns other error | Error returned |\n| Parse timestamp at exact boundary | Correct expiration computation |\n| Concurrent sandbox updates | Handled by controller-runtime optimistic locking |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [Idle Cleanup Design](idle-cleanup/design.md) — Detailed design document\n- [Idle Cleanup Spec](idle-cleanup/spec.md) — Specification with scenarios\n- [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns\n- [project.md](project.md) — Project context and architecture\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n1. ✅ Reconciler implementation correctly watches Sandbox resources\n2. ✅ Last activity annotation is read and parsed from Sandbox metadata\n3. ✅ Expiration is computed as lastActivity + 15 minutes\n4. ✅ Expired sandboxes are deleted automatically\n5. ✅ Non-expired sandboxes trigger requeue at expiration time\n6. ✅ Parse errors trigger requeue with 30s delay\n7. ✅ NotFound errors are handled gracefully\n8. ✅ Binary starts successfully with controller-runtime manager\n9. ✅ Scheme registration includes Sandbox CRD types\n10. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n11. ✅ Integration tests passing\n12. ✅ Signal-driven shutdown works correctly\n\n---\n\n*AR-018 — Module: pkg/agentd — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775879554506,"end":1775879554600}}}}
